    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for MRL 2. The six not-assessed factors are explicitly scoped out at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 4. The CFD model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The intended use scope — Class II centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass conditions, flow rates 2.5–7.5 L/min, speeds 2000–3500 RPM — is described in the bound Requirement (https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2) and Claim (https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case) nodes. Decision: Accepted.",
